# 3. Terminal & Shell Integrity (TPG Protocol)

# [CRITICAL] Zero-Shell Discovery: File search/listing/read via OS shell (dir, ls, find, Get-ChildItem, grep) is STRICTLY FORBIDDEN.
# MUST use IDE native tools ONLY:
#   find_by_name (file/folder search), grep_search (text search), list_dir (folder listing),
#   view_file (read content), write_to_file / replace_file_content (write/edit).
# Reason: Shell output is unstructured noise that pollutes Context Window, is non-deterministic across environments,
#         and causes fatal Side Effects (wrong-file delete/modify) from path mis-parsing.
# Exception: Build (npm run), type-check (tsc), package management ONLY. Even then, ls/dir MUST NOT be mixed in.

# - Environment: ALL commands MUST use `powershell.exe -NoProfile` to bypass profile interference.

# - Integrity: PowerShell(UTF-8 with BOM), Source/MD(UTF-8 no BOM), Batch(ANSI/CP949).

# - Initializers: Mandatory `Clear-Host; $env:TERM='dumb'; $env:NO_COLOR='1'; $ProgressPreference = 'SilentlyContinue'`.

# - Stability: Use `Join-Path` for OS-independent path construction; avoid hardcoded slashes.

# - Traffic: Always use `2>&1 | Select-Object -Last 30` or `| Out-Null` to prevent buffer overflow.

# - Syntax: Use `-LiteralPath` for ALL file operations to prevent wildcard interpretation errors.
# - File Guard: NEVER use Set-Location (cd) on file paths. Files → Get-Content -LiteralPath '...'.
# - Pipeline Guard: NEVER pipe Join-Path to Get-Content. Use subexpression: Get-Content (Join-Path ...).
# - CLI Arg Guard: NEVER append extra args to 'npm run lint' in monorepo roots. cd to target dir first.
# - npx Guard: NEVER use bare 'npx tsc'. Use 'npx -p typescript tsc' or define 'npm run type-check'.

