# 6. TypeScript Type Validation Protocol (Token Optimization)
# Ref: docs/TS_TYPE_VALIDATION.md (SSOT for full strategy)
#
# [MANDATORY] LLM MUST NOT perform type checking. tsc is the type checker.
# - ALWAYS run `npm run type-check` BEFORE asking LLM to fix types.
# - ONLY send to LLM: tsc error lines + ±5 surrounding code lines (Error-Only Context).
# - FORBIDDEN: sending entire .ts files for type analysis.
# - FORBIDDEN: using `any`, `@ts-ignore` or type assertions to bypass errors.
# - FORBIDDEN: writing nested Conditional Types (T extends U ? A : B extends C ? D).
# - Schema-First: Zod schema MUST precede TypeScript interface definitions.
# - Minimum Context Hierarchy: error code → failing line → direct type import chain (1 level).
# - DDD Layer: inject ONLY src/domain/index.ts (Barrel Export) as type context. Never inject services/ or repositories/.
# - Symbol Reference: reference @interface/@type symbols only, NOT @Files. Never read node_modules source — use .d.ts only.
# - Type Flatten: decompose complex infer/extends chains into named intermediate types before sending to LLM.
# - Verification: after LLM fix, re-run `npm run type-check` to confirm 0 errors.
# - Error-Slice Command (PowerShell):
#   npx -p typescript tsc --noEmit 2>&1 | Select-String "error TS" | Select-Object -First 20
# - Type Definition Extractor: scripts/types-extractor.ts (ts-morph based, definition-only output)

